OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 24 Jul to Sun 2 AugFDry
OL,6,Fon Friday for most with sunny spells.
OL,7,FNorthern and northwestern areas will
OL,8,Fbe cloudier with occasional patchy
OL,9,Frain or drizzle. Into the weekend and
OL,10,Fperhaps the start of next week, more
OL,11,Funsettled weather with rain at times,
OL,12,Fespecially across northern parts of
OL,13,Fthe UK. This rain may very well reach
OL,14,Fsouthern areas too, but could become
OL,15,Fmore light and patchy here. Confidence
OL,16,Fbecomes lower as we approach the turn
OL,17,Fof the month, but there are signs that
OL,18,Fhigh pressure will return, which means
OL,19,Fdry conditions would resume,
OL,20,Fespecially in the south. Winds will be
OL,21,Fmostly light or moderate, occasionally
OL,22,Ffresh around northern coasts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,FTemperatures are expected to be near
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,For above normal, warmest in the south,
OL,25,Fperhaps becoming very warm again by
OL,26,Fthe start of August.
